76561198135056309,Recommended,249230,15100629,"Posted: 28 March, 2015",all,MateSalsa,"I finished the game right now and well...I have mixed feelings about it. I give a thumbs up because I loved previous Risen games, and want to support the developer which is a semi indy european company, but I'm not sure if I can recommend this.Ok, the things which Piranha does great in general, does great also in this game: the atmosphere, the exploration, the humor and the side quests. AND Risen 3 does a better job in those things which are generally bad in Piranha games, like it is more polished than previous Risen games, and finally has an approachable fighting system as well, but the story is horrible as usual (even if Risen 2 had a decent story anyway).So what's the problem? The problem is that the game is not new. RIsen 1 was an interesting game, and then Risen 2 came out and was able to bring some freshness, so they were different and innovative experiences on their own.But Risen 3 is not more than Risen 1+2 with an updated Risen 2 graphics. It is disappointing even if the game is very enjoyable.Then for whatewer reason the devs cut the story and the lore of the previous games and introduced a new storyline and arch enemy. It was quiet a WTF?? What made the story more messy is that they made constant references to the happenings of the previous games even if the story line doesn't have any connection with Risen 1+2.Because the story was uninteresting I felt the game a little longer than I wanted. It is a 40+ hour game, bear in mind.So should I recommend this game? Well, if you love Piranha Bytes games and want to get all of them, you will buy it. If you enjoyed the previous games but you are not a hardcore fan don't buy it, becuase previous Risen games are better. If you hated them, you will hate also this one.But for starters maybe this is the most accessable game. It is the most polished out of the 3 ones with the best fighting system, and becuase it has a different story you don't need to play the older games to get into it.I personally enjoyed it, but I feel it completely skippable.Piranha Bytes next time you need to try harder coz ppl won't buy your games!!!"
,Recommended,249230,11743109,"Posted: 16 August, 2014",all,Phantom,"(Updated my review below)Now let me start off my review by saying that this isn't a game for casual players. If you want to mash some buttons and get through stuff alright you're gonna get frustrated and angry.People who have played Gothic and previous Risen games will feel right at home here though.The game is in many ways an improvement over Risen 2, I'll sum up all the points I think have been improved over compared to the previous game in the franchise.+ Much bigger world+ Tons of quests and things to do+ Combat at sea against sea monsters (ripped from Assassins Creed Black Flag but still nice)+ 3 different factions to join (exactly like in gothic 2, you can pick one and stuff will change according to your choice)+ Magic is back, there are tons of spells and skills for you to learn (Voodoo is back and awesome!)+ Treasure searching from Risen 2 is back in force and theres a lot of stuff for you to find+ Companions have more to say and aren't just there like in Risen 2, the game feels more alive. (They give you advice and sometimes really save your life during fights)+ Less bugs and glitches than in Risen 2 (although there are still a few minor issues)+ Gorgeous evironments! (Seriously, look at some screenshots!)+ Music and sound is perfect!+ Replayablility because of the 3 different factions (You can only join one of them so you can play the game again and experience it in a different way with different skills and everything!)+ Hilarious dialog sometimes+ Feels a lot like gothic! (no, seriously it does. The 3 different factions you can join and the overall feel of the game when you're playing is very similar. You even get good references to gothic sometimes throughout the game. Scavengers are in the game and there's a guy called Moe asking for money in front of the tavern :D and those are just a few of them.)+ Did a quest for a parrot, got 2200 gold and new armor! (10/10)Unfortunately there are a few things that just aren't that good...I love the game but in order to make this an honest game review I gotta put the negatives here too.- Voice acting is a mixed bag (For me it was fine but other players will think it's horrible)- Armor is really scarce throughout the game, you'll get your faction armor when you join one of them but that's about it.(It was pretty much the same in the gothic games though)- The game has frame rate issues- Enemy AI is horrible sometimes- ocasional pop in throughout the entire game- Some graphical glitches here and there- Clothes of npc's don't look that great sometimes (clipping)- Combat is challenging in the gothic kind of way, in the beginning you'll have to run away from enemies sometimes. If you wander off and go to deep in some parts of the islands you'll encounter monsters that are way to strong for you. Levelling is slow at first but once you're strong the game is a lot of fun. Gothic was the same and if someone says it isn't they're lying. I've finished Gothic 1 and 2 for like 3 times so I know how the games are. I don't have a problem with this but others will, thats why I said at the beginning that this isn't for casual players.Overall the game was and still is a lot of fun for me, I'll probably keep playing it for a while like I did with Risen 2. But players that aren't used to this kind of gameplay wont enjoy it as much as I did. I'm sure of that, so my advice to those people would be to play Gothic 2 or try out Risen 2. If you get annoyed as hell and hate the levelling and the overall gameplay of those 2 this isn't the game for you. It doesn't do anything new or inovative, it's made for the fans of those 2 franchises(Gothic & Risen)I give this game an 8/10Update: Just started a new game to see if things are different when you join another faction and they are. I joined the Guardians and I have a different ship and some unique faction quests as well!. I highly recommend players to try the game out a 2nd or even 3rd time to see the changes for themselves.I know I gave this game an 8/10 but there's just so many good things that i'm seeing that I'm very tempted to raise it to 9 :D"
,Recommended,249230,28132925,"Posted: 1 December, 2016",all,BrassMunkee,"I don't really review many games, but I came into this experience not really sure what to expect. I am honestly not certain why I never fell into the Gothic / Risen fanbase, it's clearly right up my ally, but Risen 3 is my first despite knowing about the following it had, for a long time.It was just great, that's all I can really say. I did whatever I wanted to do, whenever I wanted to do it, and built whatever character I wanted. There are some obvious criticisms, as any game has, but they aren't really significant enough to have distracted from how much fun I was having. The dialogue can be cheesy, but I was mostly interested in what people had to say (that's rare.) The missions had purpose, the maps and caves we're interesting.I'm not going to do a neat list of pro's and con's like other prolific reviewers. Just a damn good RPG, tons to do, tons of items, interesting magic, and a really refreshing melee combat system. Honestly. every video I see online of hard encounters we're people using rifles and the like. That seems so boring. I 1-hand melee'd my way through to the credits. You think it has quirks until you learn what's really going on and how to time your charge attacks, or parry. That aspect reminded me of the Dark Souls series. Once you git gud, it doesn't matter how much damage your weapon does or how much defense you have. Just learn it.10/10 this was a welcome surprise."
