,Recommended,249230,11684418,"Posted: 12 August, 2014",all,[TAW] Derisat Hartfelt,"*NEW REVIEW UP-New Review after 20+ hours in the game-I'm going to write this review from a Gothica/Risen fans PoV. You will have to understand PB games to appreciate this game. it is a niche game for players who like hard combat Action RPG's like Dark Souls.-For returning players from the Gothica/Risen universe, PB made a solid game in Risen 3. The engine is a more efficient less buggy redo of Risen 2, so the graphics and physics are techinaly the same but have now been recoded for less bugs, locked high frame rates, and less stress on your hardware. So if you're looking for a new top of the lin graphics engine on par with a PS4 game don't expect much. The Game was released on 360/ps3/WinPC, so it's made for last gens hardware.You play a new hero, you are not the nameless figure from Risen 1 and 2, but instead you are one of the sons of Captain Steelbeard, your sister is Patty and you start off the game together.==FOR NEW PLAYERS==Pirahna Bytes, aka PB, is known for making EXTREMELY STORY driven RPG's with DIFFICULT COMBAT mechanics. Not combat thats clunky, but combat that reflects starting off as a new character, as you gain skills in combat training you will notice the improvement and growth of your character. If you're new to this kind of game, then the start of the game (first 4 hours) will be a pain in the butt for you. But you will feel your character grow and get a real sense of accomplishment as you gain more skills and stats. It's one of the staples of PB games and it makes it a very niche genre not unlike Dark Souls is a niche genre. I highly suggest purchasing Risen 1 since it's dirt cheap and has no DLC to get a feel for PB games. if this is your first PB game and you don't like the game style you will feel ripped off, but I don't feel ripped off, I love it.==COMBAT==Combat will be more in line with Risen 1, then in Risen 2. More emphasis on dodging, and reading opponents ques, understanding when they combo attacks and when what they do when you dodge, moving in combat to avoid getting ganged up on, and choosing when to attack is key. Unlike Risen 2 you will not be able to move from Parry to Attack seamlessly, lending a step of difficulty more in line with traditional PB games. Which for PB fans is great, Risen 2 had hard reviews from PB veterans for making the game more cupcake and less hardcore. So Risen 3 is a step in the right direction.==CRAFTING==Unlike Risen 1 and 2, weapon crafting actually has a USE in this game. A new feature is that you take some of the misc items and combine them with weapons to make a better weapon (Thrusting sword + 2 silver plates+6 iron ore) gets you a Disked Epee, with better stats of couse, it is very money effecient. This is also in line with Guns, Muskets, and all melee weapons, even with the unqiue weapons that require difficult to find parts can be upgraded with lots of rare mats to make superior verions or to change it's damage type. Example the Crest Wave SLASHING sword 55-85 Damage +10 Slashing can be changed to the ""Lightning"" 55-85 Piercing +10 Piercing *and it has electric particle skin and can partialy pierces blocks*Potion crafting is back along with the rare + perm stat potions made from the perm stat ingredients, The raw ingredients give +2, the potions give +5More emphasis on temp buff potions is used since there are more skills to allocate your Glory(XP) too. So expect to use buff potions often to surpass early Lockpicks, Persuade, and Pickpocket checks==GAME LENGTH==24.5 Hours into the game at the time of this review, i am still in chapter 2, I have 4 islands explored,  2 islands un explored, and just started my 5th island. Like a good book, PB games tend to have 3 acts, I have not chosen one of the 3 factions available yet, and don't expect too until I'm near the end of chapter 2. I have only encountered 2 of the main factions so far. The games factions are the Guardians/Mages from Risen 1, the Voodoo Pirates from Risen 2, and the new faction are the Demon Hunters. You will spend hours revisting islands to find more quests, NPC's, loot, buried treasures, and open hidden passages. These do not feel like tacked on back tracking to add game time thank goodness, but honest progression, both in character development and story. I expect to drop 40-55 hours on the campaign easily.==OVER ALL IMPRESSION SCORE==Using 10/10 as a base line for Risen 1Gothica 3 beng 9/10and 6/10 as a Baseline for Risen 2and 4/10 as Gothic 4: Arcaniaand 1/10 being Daikatana or Superman 64I give Risen 3 a 8.5/10Graphics 7/10The graphics are last gen but RECENT last gen, so they are smooth FPS on Max graphics and are plenty pretty, PB games aren't known for shiny, they are known for superb story and gameplay.Combat 9/10Not as varied or complex as Risen 1, it is much better then Risen 2, you can still feel your character grow, and get that sense of accomplishment. PB vets/fans should play on HARD. Pb did a great job getting back to it's roots.Story 10/10Well written and capable of being a book, deep and lengthy but not stale, and a continuation from Risen 1 and 2. It's fantastic, a game with great plot, it is perfect for the Single Player western RPG fans who miss plot.Is this game worthy of the PB saga? Yes it is, it is a redeeming light for PB since the goofs of Gothica 4 and Risen 2. A great sign that they are getting back in touch with what made them our favorites. I would compare Risen 3 with Deus Ex 3 in terms of taking a step in the proper direction to it's roots.Is the game worth the 49.99 USD price tag? YES, most new games cost 59.99 USD, some Early Access games cost as much as 125 USD and are utter crap. 10 dollars cheaper the most AAA games and a positive growth in game style for PB fans makes this a steal!PB vets should buy Risen 3 if you are on the ropes.NEW PB PLAYERS should buy Risen 1 or Gothica 1,2 or 3 to see if this is the game style you;d enjoy. Feel free to read my review for Risen 1 to see what I mean.*DAY 1 OLD REVIEW*Finished my third island. taking I'm taking a break to write a short early impression. I like the game so far, the combat early on was dissapointing but it picked up soon. i restarted a new game and made the entire first level without getting hit onceIt's closer to risen 1 in combat then risen 2. Main difference, you can't go from Parry to attack, and you use dodging a lotOnly found one bug and it's in quest text, there in Antigua, you'll have to find a bag of clothes and it says it's on the FIRST floor, it's actually on the 2nd floor, use a parrot flight to get thereI am dissapointed that damage types aren't damage styles, now all weapons swing like slashing weapons, makes the fencer in me sadi play on hard difficulty, the game is still fairly easy, about on par with risen 2. the soft 50 fps lock is nice. It's superior to risen 2 in story, size and gameplay, i need to play more to compare it to risen 1. if i had to review score it based on the first 4 hours. 8/10 but I'm not into the meat of the story line yetPatty broke my heart, they got rid of her curly long black hair, and I'm her god damn brotherI wanted to continue as the nameless hero and finaly get her in the damn sack!It's a solid game, and worth the 49.99 USD, which need i remind people is not the usual 59.99 of most games. If you played both Risens and liked risen 1 better, you'll like this game. not as much as 1 but more then 2. I think it was worth the purchaseOn to Fog Island next to get the 10% Glory special item"
