,Recommended,249230,11737968,"Posted: 16 August, 2014",all,Augustus,"5/5Gameplay:+ Oriented on Gothic 1&2 and Risen 1+ Same humor as ever+ Very much atmosphere, in terms of quests and the game/level/island design.+ I can not! confirm, that the quests are generic or anything like that. Also every character has it's own personality and position in this game, there are only very few unnamed characters with no kind of background in this world. But this does not only to npcs, but to all items and locations aswell, truly handcrafted!+ I love the way magic got implemented in this game! No exhausting mana-potion collection or brewing which I always disliked, but just a cooldown-based system. Some critisize that, I love it and think a lot of games should go that direction!+ I do not find the story boring and do not agree with (most) reviewers.+ I love flying or gliding around like a parrot.- Sometimes there's not enough feedback whether a quest is completed, failed or still pending in status, e.g. before being promoted to a guardian you have to talk to your pirate admiral. He then tells you to kill the undead dogs, swirling around the city. Although this is not hard to accomplish, one may still miss out on some dogs and ask him-/herself, why one can't get promoted. Another example would be the ""di fuego"" related quests.- Sometimes npcs can't follow you and get stuck, however if you wait long enough they will eventually be back at your position (Teleporting and/or going back to your ship or another island helps in this case).Graphics:+ I don't know where to start. All people critizing the graphic of risen 3 can't have played it.+ I have rarely seen such beautiful sunsets and sunrises as in this game. Just as an example if one stands a bit away from the council hall or tower in antigua and in front of it, and if it's dawn and you look up in the sky, you see the air glimming inside the council hall, with a warm fire enlightening the whole building and if you look up, you have this dark, star filled sky, which at the very edge slowly fades into a warm pink/purpleish kind of color. There were countless moments like that and I can truly say that I have met no game, where the graphic is that atmospheric, some of the steam-screenshots catch very well how beautiful the game looks!- I mean, yes, sometimes!!! there are very low resolution textures, but most of the time they don't catch the eye.Sound:0 Well, there has been written a lot about this part of the game so I will skip the extensive part and sum up that although I also find that the sound is very atmospheric, there are some downsides.+ The german synchronization however is very well!To sum it up: If you liked the Gothic series and Risen 1, buy it. The basis for this game may be a pirate setting and of course it plays in the Risen universe, but it catches the Gothic flair from old times quite well and has some (good) adjustments to it.Also I have not played Risen 2 so I can't say which textures got reused etc.One last comment I want to make is, that most of the negative reviews seem to be from people that have played the game only a few hours and could not immerse themselfs in it, whether it is because their personal taste of a game is different or because they were not patient enough. I also think that this is reflected pretty well in the metacritics score which has a lot of negative reviews, but just as much positive reviews and nothing in between, so this game really splits based on your personal taste."
76561198050768921,Recommended,249230,18382883,"Posted: 8 October, 2015",all,ChrisMcKennaCMK,"Nice game, pretty faithful to old Gothic style and lots of pirates and what not.On the plus side, it got a nice environment, varied ways to play, lots of hidden things to find and some interesting characters. For the most part the story is enjoyable and fast paced and the leveling up style make you have to plan ahead.The downside, story can be a little 2D in places. The game is fairly challenging at the beginging, but if you complete all the quests you get pretty over powered by the end and things get a bit repetative - the last island really could have done with a whole new set of monsters. Likewise weapons/equipment could have done with a lot more variation.It's not perfect by any means, but if you enjoy an fun RPG where you wander round exploring it's pretty good."
