76561198018110605,Recommended,249230,11841622,"Posted: 23 August, 2014",all,DAVOS,"7.5/10Fun game, like the previous ones. Great story, let down by some dodgy voice acting and stilted dialogue. Some of the gnome voices are on the Jarjar Binks end of the annoying spectrum. Sometimes they verge on casual racism, sometimes they say funny things. It's like they are trying to do bad asian accents and sound ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ at the same time. There are some notable exceptions to that criticism. I thought the characterisation of ""Stax"" was done very well.Some criticize the combat system, and I can see why you'd love it or hate it as it requires a little patience. It's real-time-turn-based, if that's a thing; similar to the Gothic games. It's not a mindless hack-n-slash so you need to time blows, blocks and dodging. It's generally easy with one opponent but gets quickly impossible with 3 or more. You need a party to act as combat decoys more than you need them to assist you in fighting.The lore is a bit of a grab-bag but I enjoyed the pirate/inquisitor/voodoo/druid/mage/aztec ruin/underworld thing they mashed together. I like sandbox sprawlers that let you jump up to seemingly inaccessible places and reward you with hidden loot. There's no character creation, but it also doesn't lock you in to classes so your character will end up evolving towards the skills you like using.Very playable RPG fun....After 70+ hours of game play, I can say it's well worth it given the price on release was around half of what a premium game would be. There's some amusing quirks that are either poor translations or dev in-jokes, for example every single bird yields chicken drumsticks. I suppose everything tastes like chicken.What I said about classes, well you don't need to hold back, you can max out a lot of skills by the end so there's no compromises. There are 3 guilds to join, I played mage because lightening, but going back I'd probably have a go at demon hunter. Voodoo is powerful but to be honest that was my least favourite part of the game.Pirate Patty's boobs are ridiculous. And she's supposed to be your sister, thanks Borat. I recall the character from a previous Risen, but I don't recall her being dressed like a pirate-stripper on halloween. I love boobs but really, it was a bit out of place. Witcher did that way better.They swear a lot too. I spose it's pirates, but if you're gonna swear do it well."
