,Recommended,249230,29059036,Posted: 6 January,all,WindRider739,"If you enjoyed the Gothic franchise, you're going to love this game.I won't lie to you and say it has the best graphics for its time, because it doesn't. They're mediocre at best.The voice acting is some of the worst I've seen since Daikatana.The combat is a bit clunky, but once you understand the subtle nuances of timed combat, and learn the patterns of the different enemies, it's actually quite enjoyable.The story is alright; with better voice acting it might even be pretty good.Here's the thing, though... This is basically Gothic 3 (without the awful frames / freezing bug), except you're a pirate. There aren't a lot of games like that out there. Additionally, the sea combat is wonderful. If you don't really enjoy the genre, this game isn't going to be for you. However, if you love this sort of game - your elder scrolls, your gothics (before 4), or earlier Risen titles - this game is going to be a blast. It's very open in that it doesn't force you to visit places in a set order. You can go just about anywhere right from the start, and the different gameplay styles and factions give it a fair amount of replayability. Overall, I'd give this game a 3/5. For me personally, though, it's a 5/5. It just comes down to what you're into and what you're willing to put up with."
