,Recommended,249230,11772422,"Posted: 18 August, 2014",all,Xan,"If you liked the Gothic series and Risen, and can stomach the pirate theme of Risen 2, this game is for you.It was, as usual for PB, made for the audience that enjoyed their previous work.PositivesThe game is beatiful in my opinion, shaders and reflections are some of the best I've seen in a long time. Game runs mostly solid 60fps on my system (660ti and a first gen i7), dips rarely went lower than to 50fps, max settings.Combat system really did see improvements, even though many reviewers fail to see them.The new islands are much larger (at least 2 times the space and 3 times the quest density) than the two taken from Risen 2, ( the islands many criticized for being copy pasted, which is only really half-true, they have been noticably reworked and don't play as of a role in the story, I spent as much time on both of them as I did doing one half of one of the three main islands)The UI has never worked this well; instant response times and logical structure make necessary UI navigation easyNegativesThe sea battles are half baked at best, luckily they didn't take up more than 5-10 minutes at a time for me. Shame one of them starts off the game, so you see shoddy scripted animations and QTE's as a first impression, when either are rather rare throughout the entire gameWhile most of the UI is very snappy and responsive, the Inventory system is on a list basis, so scrolling is necessary. I prefered the Risen 1 system of a big open square based inventory, but I did get used to it easily.The overarching story is, as usual, quite cheesy and uninspired. That said: Obligatory ""hero looses his abilities"" we come to expect from PB games twist is probably better executed than in most previous iterations. Nice set pieces, areas and generally diverse side quests though.English voice acting is mediocre to 'meh', with many characters, german v/o is decent for a german v/o, many characters voices dont really fit their characters though. Many german voices are by voice actors that were in RIsen 1 and subsequently in the old Gothic games, so nostalgia bonus.That's really the biggest point, nostalgia bonus. If you liked Risen and loved Gothic, like I did, I would recommend, for anyone else, you may wish to wait for a sale."
