,Recommended,249230,30581833,Posted: 17 March,all,ftstani,"If you enjoyed the Gothic series, you will enjoy this game. Risen 3 represents the latest incarnation of that long long of role-playing games. If you haven't heard of the Gothic series, or Piranha Bytes, or JoWooD Entertainment, chances are that you will not enjoy Risen 3. By the standards of modern RPGs made by U.S. developers, Risen 3 is archaic.Gameplay can be boiled down to fetch quests and go-there-and-kill-that quests. But when you think about it all RPGs boil down to that. Combat is clunky by modern standards. In fact I knew this already and didn't bother playing combat and cheated, giving myself all requisite skills to avoid the frustration of constant stun-locks and whatnot. Plenty of wise sages before me has described the problems at length. The only remotely interesting aspect is the morality system. Good deeds result in soul gains, resulting in good guy rewards. Bad deeds result in soul losses, resulting in bad guy rewards (which are still rewards, so that's more realistic than most RPGs). Don't expect anything like the Witcher 3.Visually, it looks nice for a 2014 release. Some parts still look stunning, like the forest regions. Just don't expect FarCry.The story's serious parts, much like the serious characters, consist of non-descript, entirely forgettable, and highly generic fantasy tropes. You couldn't get more vanilla if you tried. There's a Dark Lord of course. However, the game is made much more spicier (and racier) by its non-serious parts, thanks in no small part to the fact that the main character is basically a pirate. Or privateer to be more accurate.Finally, you should be aware that Risen 3 is pretty sexist and racist by the standards of modern American politically correct non-triggering entertainment values. For example, I ran into two quests where the awards were sex with women, without even trying (incidentally if you're trying to be a good guy -- just remember that obvious harlots cannot be trusted!), and the only female crewmember is my hot sister strutting about in her tights and lovely bust. She is generally useless, except that she's very good at acquiring the locations of treasure by ""being nice"" to ornery old pirates. What is not useless is my gnome companion, Jaffar, who likes to steal gold and loots my defeated enemies. We also have an IQ differential that is comparable to our height differential. Jaffar is a good chap though, speaks with a strange accent and talks about his gnome buddies, named Kasim and Ali. Besides the gnomes, you also meet Voodoo natives who I swear are from Africa, with the spiritualism of Native Americans (as interpreted by modern old-worlders), but I'm surely mistaken. In any case, all of these things put together have caused many butt-hurt game reviewers to complain that the game is racist and sexist. Funny as hell though.By the way I applaud Patty's pants because they're low-rise."
