76561197971663658,Recommended,249230,18499870,"Posted: 16 October, 2015",all,alkemmy,"Having played 14 hours of ther game, I've had to revise my opinion downwards.  Still a recommended deal if you can get it 75% off, but it's not worth full whack. It's a few steps improved over Risen 2, but sadly still suffers from jerky movement and scrolling control -- easy enough for the programmers to fix by upping the screen refresh, but they don't seem to take such suggestions on board, despite just about every review of earlier games going on about it.  As you progress through the learning curve, and get used to the awkward klunky combat control, you wait in constant expectation of the game getting better -- but it doesn't.  It's island hopping and running chores for NPCs who can't do simple tasks themselves.  ""Rough round the edges"", but for the discounted price, it's a steal.  Dialogue has clearly been recorded at different studio sittings rather than sequentially and often doesn't flow smoothly, or share environmental reverb effects, or even mesh sensibly.There's some minor humour in this dry game when Mud joins the team, but only because he's an annoying pest and a hindrance.  All integrity leaves the game if and when you choose to become a ""Voodoo Pirate"", that's just silliness, but alas it may be necessary to progress the levels if you can't make headway joining the mages.  Some quests won't resolve -- bugs in the code -- so don't expect to rattle through this one on autopilot.They've back-pedaled in gameplay processes to Risen 1, which it resembles a bit too much.  Worth investing in Risen 1 if you haven't got it, as it's the stand-out of the 3 games so far."
76561198039489127,Recommended,249230,19280803,"Posted: 25 November, 2015",all,raven,"First of all, let me emphasize that this is a Piranha Game in all aspects. Which is good for me, but apparently does not fit well with some people.I started playing Piranha Games with Gothic 1 and played every game since, so I knew what to expect and am happy to report that the NPCs talk at length about trivial things and have to be forced to get to the point, you only get a fixed set of useful Armor that is restricted to your Group etc.A lot of people apparently don't like this, but for me that's a Piranha Game. If you liked the first two Gothics, this game is for you.Warning: From here on there might be SpoilersAs a long-time fan, here's what I think about Risen 3 compared to the Gothic series and the other two Risens:I loved it. It reminded my why I fell in love with Gothic and I am going to play it again to see the way the game goes if you choose to be something else then a Voodoo-Pirate.In comparison to Risen 2 I think it's much better. Which is great, as I thought Risen 2 was way better then Risen 1, so this seems to be a trend.Even the usually sucking Piranha Final Boss Battle was bearable. As a reminder, in Risen 1 the final Boss Battle neglected all your ""life choices"" and stuck you into magic Armor and Weaponry that made you a great fighter, even if you had gone the Mage way and put you into some kind of Arcade-Battle against a Big-Boss. Ugh.Risen 2 had Mara, but I only remember from that fight that I didn't like it.This time, it had sucking moments, sure. But I could play to my strengths I acquired during the game and at one point Bones jumped in to save the day, which I assume was a bug, but I liked it.Compared to the Gothic Series I dare say this is the game I was hoping for when Gothic 3 came out. It had all the charm, wits and anecdotes that made the first two Gothic Parts great and none of the empty world and hastily crafted Quests. Playing Risen 3 I couldn't but think of how great a game Gothic 3 could have been if it came out a year later. Even half a year.So all good? Of cause not. There are a lot of things they can do better and I hope they will for Risen 4. But none of the following ""bad stuff"" really impacted my great experience, so read them as ""minor issues"".The Bad stuff- I love the Kila, but hate the Post-Imperialistic, ""noble savage"", ""half naked exotic beauty that speaks in Umpa-Lumpa"" stile. You can do better than just throwing together all the cliche to mix up a ""tribe"".- Whatever happened to Patty? Why does she look like some Pirate-Porn Star? Honestly, this kind of ""Fan Service"" makes me feel treated like a 14 year old with a puberty issue. I see what you thought I would like and feel dirty.- Where's my Marvin Mode? One of the really cool things about Piranha Games was the ""and now I will change everything to how I like it"" Marvin Mode. Missed it greatly. Reduces replay-value. Basically, give me back my Marvin Mode.- If I have to hear Bones say ""Aus deiner Haut mache ich mir eine Mütze!"" one more time...- I would have liked a way to solve the Noise behind Paula's house without killing the armadillo.- Light. I know this does not happen to everyone, but every time I entered a cave darkness took me like a black flood that even torches could not dispense. Looting caves without telekinesis was basically impossible as I could not see anything smaller then a sword.- Story-restriction to Voodoo body-snatching. I get that this could be a story breaker, but there have to be better ways to restrict this then simply allowing it only if it fits the narrative.The ""meh"" StuffThese things I could go without* Astral View. Never used it. No idea why I would or should have.The Great Stuff+ The World. I liked to just hang out with the Pirates on Kila or the Kila on Kila (Reaaallly smooth...) or...+ The Characters. There are no Diegos, but a lot of likeable NPCs and taking some of them along was great fun.+ The Story. It was easy to follow without being too predictable. Yeah, there was obviously some arch-nemesis going to be there for the surprisingly minor-sucking End Battle, but other then that I liked it. Quests were mostly fun too.+ Easy mode that means ""easy fights"" for people like me who take fighting as a ""have to do that"" in RPGs+ Mud. Yeah, really. Loved it. Even took him along after he left on his own free will. That's how it goes with old “friends”...++ Parrot-Flight. You'll know it when you get it. I've spend hours flying around."
