,Recommended,249230,11933103,"Posted: 31 August, 2014",all,Jonaleth,"Don't let the metacritic rating fool you, but don't expect BioWare quality either.Risen 3 is a solid and competent roleplaying game.  Featuring a decent magic and combat system, interesting variations on ""classess"" (factions within the game), interesting and attractive environments, a good looting and gear system and a good chunk of play time, its a game that can be easily enjoyed with a little patience and forgiveness.  The leveling system is complex and interesting, asking you to increase stats to be able to learn perks and improvements to your combat abilities, which can be bought from trainers scattered all over the world.What is wrong with the game are niggles and annoyances more than bugs or bad concepts, and even then are only highlighted because we, as consumers, have come to expect things that aren't provided here.  For example, the story told in the game is threadbare and confusing, never coherently explaining what's going on or why we should care.  This is only exacerbated by the  dubious voice acting, particularly by your own character who speaks in a constant gruff monotone.  There are allusions to the past games that can make it even more confusing, such as a cameo by the past two games protagonist that should be foreshadowing and cool but is instead just strange.The dialogue options are not the range you would expect for an RPG, giving you little choice and little chance to actually roleplay, being limited to gruff piratey responses rather than varied.  The combat system takes some getting use to, and requires a combination of attack, dodge, parry and riposte, and enemies have a tendency to mob you even when there are other characters attacking them, resulting in a lot of constant dodging and pot shots until their ranks are thinned and you're back in control.  This can sometimes be exacerbated by clipping problems, or the mobile camera being blocked by scenery.Overall, Risen 3 is worth playing and enjoyable if your expectations aren't too high, and I would recommend playing it when the price drops to a level that is better value for money."
