,Recommended,249230,21382390,"Posted: 22 February, 2016",all,Ian Storm,"Risen 3 - Titand Lords(Scroll down for a tl;dr version.)As a fan of the classic Gothic series I was really looking forward for this game, since I heard that Piranha Bytes got back the rights of the Gothic series. And also, when I started playing this game, I was not disappointed regarding this aspect; I was amazed by all the elements and jokes that I knew from Gothic. Finally, I could fight some Scavengers again. But this is not what makes it a good game. Actually, I was uncertain about liking or disliking the game.Pros:+ Level/map design: There are caribbean-like islands in the south, and ""not-so-sunny"" islands, like an island with swamp, a somehow big forest or partially wasteland (with lava and burnt down trees)+ Very much related to the previous point: Exploration. I am pretty sure that I did all possible quests, that I collected every piece of loot, and I did not even get tired of it. And still there was room for more, because it did not use the parrot a lot.+ Incredible high amount of quests+ The fractions: I liked the division of the voodoo pirates, the wardens and the demon hunters. Not only stupid bad guys from king's army and good guys from the rebels.+ They finally gave me some Gothic-feeling again:E.g. you can screw around with some peasants or Jack who was kicked out of his light-house, like in Gothic II.+ Something that I found out too late: The evil dialog options are really funny. I really laughed when I was mad at some of the gnomes. (E.g. the one that is enslaved, where you could go and tell him ""Sorry, but I needed the money."" After you got paid for not telling anybody that he is enslaved.)Cons:- The so called ""story"": Like in Risen 1, the end of the game feels artificially stretched. Risen 2 did this far better. Not only this, the story is just weak in total.- Combat system- Difficulty level far too low( - Despite the environment's variety, there is no snow level :'( )Risen 3 is, in my opinion, not a milestone in the history of RPGs. But it does quite a good job. Also, I would not have thought about thumbs down, if there wasn't this horrible last island. Why did the developers think like ""For the end of the story, let's build the f***ing largest island, tell the hero that time is running out so bad, but still there is time to run from one side of the island to the other, just to find some camps, that aren't even useful."" Seriously Piranha Bytes, what the f**k?Moreover, you (the developers) could have just let Eldric and the other two die. I really would have prefered it in this way. But no, even in the hardest fight in the history of humans, no ""important"" characters dies (excluding Horas). That is a childish story.But I was able to spend around 70 hours of fun with that game, which I pretty much like (Until now I spend 80h playing this game. So 10h of ""not-fun"".)Sorry, if you expected more Gothic related information. In the draft I had much of this stuff, but I decided to remove these things more or less completely. I think I would have to replay Gothic I and II, to being capable of giving a fair review.TL;DRDid you enjoy playing Risen and Risen 2? Then you will most likely also enjoy this game. Because Risen 3 feels like a good extension to the pirate setting of Risen 2. If you don't like becoming a pirate or a voodoo priest, just become a mage or demon hunter, which I think are like the dragon hunters from Gothic II."
