76561197979747603,Not Recommended,249230,34237941,Posted: 14 August,all,Darth Cannabis,"While it may be a good title on its own for someone who has never played 1 or 2, I just cannot recomend it, being a fan of previous installments in the series. There are just too many signs, where I see it havign been dumbed down for console for me to ignore past an hr into the game. If you want to feel like a pirate and enjoy part of the series for that reason, I recomend 2 over 3, many times over.One of the 1st things to turn my stomach, is the oversized HUD and text elements comapred to previous games. I understand why this is (people on tvs, typically sit further back, or the tv may jsut be small), but to me its just one of those little reasons why I believe in PC games developed for PC, and console for console. If you do cross develop, then do that little extra effort to distinquish the 2 mediums. Don't be lazy, and ruin a good PC set up.The 2nd thing, is Patty. Different clothing fine. Different hair, not thrilled but is explainable (dyes and coloring are often picked up by pirates from natives), but how drastically all the changes to her are is a shame. Wrong body structure, facial structure, eye color, complection, and so on. Even her attitude seems wrong. That character designer should have been physically punished.Then we get to the combat system, which contrary to what some say I find is NOT better than previous games. To compare just to 2, parry and block were not the same thing in that. They seem to have just made parry and block same in 3. Giant Crabs were not just knocked over with a power attack, but you had to learn a kick skill to do so, which added another tactical aspect to the sword fighting. For example, the kick was also good as a quick knock back on ghouls after their 3 hits, to open a window for a power attack, or to knock back a jaguar for a pistol shot on it, etc. Instead combat in 3 has been reduced to attack, power attack, block (I am calling it, since as explained, block and parry used to be more separate, but also an slightly off timed parry would result in a feint like dodge that WAS NOT A ROLL.) and roll (which is something I loathe in games. A true swordsman would see it as ONLY a last resort, as the moment you leave your feet your on a set tragectory and easy target for a quick stab or slash.)Then we get to the enemies themselves. They even seem somewhat dumbed down. Remember coming across your 1st warriors in 2? They likely killed you, or you had to run and retreat. 1st warriors you come to in 3? A complete joke. Giant Crabs, whiel never a major threat, have become more of a joke. Only saving grace is ghouls seem to not have changed."
