76561197993756185,Not Recommended,249230,13651815,"Posted: 27 December, 2014",all,Cunnilingus Academy,"The only reason I am not recommending this game is it's price tag... the quality of this game is NOT up to par with other titles in the $49.99 price range. I purchased the game during the Holiday sale when it was $24.99, and personally, I believe that's about what this game is worth. I'll list off some things that bothered me and, yes, I understand I've only played the game for about an hour... but that hour alone gave me enough ""feel"" for the game to know that I simply do not enjoy playing it and I probably will not boot it up again.1. The intro was rushed, and it felt cheap and plagurized.A. You start off on a boat sailing to who knows where, from who knows where (possibly this information is known if you've played Risen 2, which I haven't, but I still had no idea what was going on in the beginning of the game), and seemingly out of no-where, you're attacked by pirate sea creatures STRAIGHT out of Pirates of the Caribbean. I don't have the slightest doubt in my mind that the artists had pictures from PotC up on google as they designed these guys.B. During this intro, the game briefly shows you how to move and look around, jump, attack, unsheath your weapon, shoot your gun, dodge, etc. The controls just feel off to me. If this makes sense, which I hope it does to some of you out there; there are just some games out there with controls so fine-tuned that you could do an obsticle course, jump from object to object, avoid things swinging at you, etc, with ease (think TF2, CS:GO, CoD, Skyrim). In this game there is no way in hell I would be able to jump from object to object or dodge ANYTHING, the controls feel that lousy and unsynced. A side note added onto that... when I hold down the sprint key... I want to sprint NOW, not after a delay of 1 second.2. The story. (FIRST HOUR SPOILER)From what I understood, you're a pirate on a jouney with your sister who, by coincidence, has huge jugs, The intro lets you play through getting attacked by a ship of sea creature pirates captained by a ""Ghost pirate""... who, after losing all of his men onboard to your sword, summons Gyarados which ♥♥♥♥s your♥♥♥♥♥♥up and you're stranded on an Island straight out of the TV series ""Lost"". It then seems your objective is to find or chase down the pirate ghost... at least for the beginning part of the game. I didn't get that far.3. Voice acting.Imagine the worst home made movie you've ever seen, then imagine paying those people each $1,000 to actually try to act. That's about what the voice acting is like.4. Looting, ""Open world"", other RPG elements.A. The looting system is very off from traditional RPGs. Yes, I get games can be different from others, etc, and that's cool, that's awesome, but not having a menu pop up when you go to loot a creature and instead having it auto loot everything and spam the side of your screenRECIEVED SPIRIT MUSHROOM x 1 !RECIEVED RAW MEAT x 1 !RECIEVED CLAM x 1 !RECIEVED GOLD x 1000!GLORY + 200can get annoying. Strangely enough, however, if you go to loot a container, you ARE given a menu and the choice to loot whatever's in the container.B. Despite claiming to be open world, the game is still very linear. To put into perspective, Skyrim is the obvious king of open world games, you can literally go ANYWHERE. The Witcher 2, on the other hand, is pretty linear, and isn't necessarily open world. This game isn't remotely close to The Witcher 2, and is about as linear as a CoD campaign.C. Other RPG elements such as how the inventory is managed, quests, maps, etc... it all works, but it all feels cheap and rushed.In conclusion, the Risen fanboys will hate me and my review, but crossing over from other RPG's like the Elder Scrolls series, the Diablo series, the Borderlands series, etc, I was not prepared for the incredibly, insultingly, low quality of the game.TL;DR: If you're coming from Skyrim, Borderlands, Diablo, Mass Effect, The Witcher... (all high quality and finely tuned RPGs), and looking for something new whilst staying in the RPG scene, stay away from Risen 3."
