,Not Recommended,249230,17754973,"Posted: 28 August, 2015",all,*^Matt^*,"This is one of the worst RPGs I ever played with the most infuriating combat system ever.  I'm glad I got this on the sale as I would be extremely annoyed had I paid the full RRP for this trash.  First off the voice acting on the main character is the worst I have ever heard on any game, let alone an RPG.  It is truly dreadful and the writing is just as bad, it is like some 12 year old who just learnt the F word had written the script.  Within only an hour or 2 of playing the bad voice acting and writing had already started to grate one me.Then there is the truly awful combat system.  The tutorial shows you how to parry and do combos and is set up so you can do that in the tutuorial but good luck actually trying to do that in the game.  For a start parrying seems to have no effect on beasts like rock spiders and scavengers so the combat ends up with constant dodging and then hitting the LMB to get a quick slash of the sword in which takes precious little health off whatever you are fighting in the beginning before you are dodging again.  This isn't challenging, it is extremely tedious when it seems to take near enough 20 hits to take out various creatures at the start of the game.  It doesn't lend itself well when you are outnumbered either as sooner or later you end up rolling into a strike from 1 of the 3 enemies you end up being surrounded by frequently.  Then of course if you happen to dodge in to vegetation you can't see what is going on resulting in being struck again.  Your character is also slow to respond to the LMB and often gets hit before completing the strike and yet your enemies seem to be able to jump backwards at alarming speed so many of your strikes don't hit home.  This makes one on one tedious enough but being outnumbered even more so and I quickly found myself going through provisions and rum, even on the easy setting just because I don't have the patience to spending an hour on each fight constantly dodging and rolling around the place. I don't get the reviews complaining how OP your character gets - I found him hideously underpowered at the start just trying to do the tedious quest of going to all the mines in order to join the guardians when having to go through seemingly undending rock spiders, shadow warriors and hellhounds.  After just 4 hours playing I have had enough of the game already with the immensely repetitive dodge/strike nonsense.The only positive is that the game does look nice but with the dreadful combat system and equally bad voice acting (at least from the main character) I can't recommend this game, in fact I would save time and money and don't buy it in the first place."
