,Not Recommended,249230,11714555,"Posted: 15 August, 2014",all,Foxes hunting hounds,"If you really liked Risen 1 & 2 and/or the Gothic series, try it. But don't go in there with somewhat high expectations.The story is something between AC4 and Pirates of the Caribbean. Not deep, not shallow, not very original. The phrasing of Quests didn't impress me positively. I'm sure there would've been another way than ""Next Quest: Pull on the lever"". ""Open the temple door"" could've sounded a little tiny bit better.I'm playing with a controller (don't give me♥♥♥♥♥♥for that, it's easier to handle than a mouse with a wrist beyond repair), and it's just frustrating.Controls are clunky and it's responding late or not at all sometimes. Press the block button - get hit - block. Dodging in the direction you want? Eeeh, I'll try my best and- whoops got hit. I ended up spamming the Dodge button in every fight.Have your weapon drawn and want to open a door or pick up loot? No. Away with your weapon, manually. In a painfully slow animation. Something attacks you and is already in your face? Press B. Then A. Got hit? Too bad. Kind of like the chinese blackmarket rip-off of Assassin's Creed's combat.The camera's jerking around making it almost impossible to adjust it to your likings: A slight tilt to the left with the joystick results in a complete turn around-up-down-left-right making it stupidly hard to see or hit any enemy. Even without your doing, it'll just zoom in or out at the worst times. Fighting in a tight spot and dodging, against a wall because you can't really control the direction, and you're done for. It's no help to have a close up on that stone behind me, really.Lots of unneccesary small cut scenes. Opening a chest is fine, but I do not need to see the same kneeling down-opening chest-looking inside every goddamn time. They tried to make a kill cam as well, but it only takes time and isn't anything special. I'd rather do without. Accidentally facing Patty and pressing A results in yet another short cut scene whereas she tells you 'Not now, later' most of the time. Voice acting makes it all the worse.First look, the world looks like it's been modelled with lots of love. Second look, not so much. The screenshots are deceiving in my opinion - I just recently built this PC. The best of the best, because I like nice looking games, and i certainly want them to run smoothly.This however, I could play on my Mothers Laptop and it would still look the same. The highest settings are a joke. It's atmospheric, don't get me wrong, But not aesthetic. If you told me that this game came out in 2008, I'd believe you.And OH MY GOD how slow do you have to walk. That is ridiculous. Running ain't better."
