,Not Recommended,249230,17866946,"Posted: 3 September, 2015",all,DracoMalus,"The best looking game in the series but the laziest and weakest overall.Except for the visuals there really isn't anything that's improved since Risen 2 and much has gotten worse.The Good:I like the visuals, the enhanced edition really looks good.  The models, the colors, and the overall look and feel of the environments are well done.  There are are few small anomalies here and there but nothing horrible or overly distracting.  Weather effects could be a bit better, but it doens't really take away anything.I like the magic.  While I haven't used all the systems if the others are similay to the way voodoo works then that's pretty good.  While magic isn't a very in depth process it's interesting and diverse enough to be fun to use.I have always liked the quest system, where you can complete the goals of a quest even before you get assigned the quest.  So if you kill all the creatures in some corner and then come across a guy who gives you the quest to go kill the creatures in that corner, you can complete it right then and there.Some minor (and major) rewards for exploring.  I like being able to look up at some rocks and ask ""What's up there?"" and much of the time I am able to clime up there and find something there; a dead body, some gold or food, or whatever.  Very rarely have I been disappointed from randomly exploring the areas.The BadSo mcuh of in this game is left over from the previous games.  Very little is completely new.  You'll interact with just about everyone you met before in the previous games, many of these meetings are forced and add absolutely noting to the plot. Especially the ones you meet in your very short stints into the underworld which are forced upon you at various times when you go to sleep.  Boring and a complete waste of time.Combat still sucks♥♥♥♥♥  You pretty much have the same moves you did in Risen 2 and most of the enemies still use the same tired old attack routines.  Save for a couple of the newer mini bosses and bosses every creature uses the same attack pattern that existed in previous game.  It truly boggles my mind that an alligator has teh exact same attack pattern as the wild beaked birds. Combat adds almost nothing new in installment.  Even my voodoo combat is the same as my melee combat save that it will hit multiple creatures rather than just one.  Not to mention even on hard this game is easy save for the random times the AI just goes ballistic and starts throwing up a stream of attacks there is no way you can defend against.  Also, some monsters, despite how powerful your armor is, will kill in one hit if you fail to dodge.  Combat is an annoying chore instead of a fun activity.Auto saves:  Autosaves are nice, but they are very strangely activated.  Most are okay, but there are times where they should be used when they're not.  An autosave should activate right a fast travel and tehy aren't.  If you forget to save after a fast trave to your ship and then travel to another island and then get killed by something on the beach, when you reload you'll be way back on that other island.  Also, I have encounterd puzzles where once you solve them you get ambushed and if you don't save and get killed you have to solve the puzzle again.  One took me 10 minutes to solve and I got ambushed, die almost instantly, and had to redo the god damn puzzle.  That's a horrible flaw.  Autosave on complete puzzles is a must.Vague quest resolution:  A few quests are completely vague in how they are supposed to be resolved.  One in particular I have done every single quest on the isle of mages and all I get is ""I still have soem things to do before we can start"" with absolutely no clue what I need to do or am waiting for.Companions:  Kinda hand for combat, though they're really slow to start fighting (I can fimish most foes before the companion even makes one attack) they are almost always in your way when you wanna loot the corpses.  You have to specifically make sure the corpse is highlighted because you companion will usually be right here in your face when trying to loot.  This is annoying as hell.The underworld:  Often times when you sleep you're whisked away into a stint in the underworld which serves one of two purposes.  So you can have a brief chat with someone you killed in Risen 2 which adds nothing to the game in the least and another to collect ""soul dust"" which can help elevate your soul rank, but they always end abruptly as you collect one or two and then a creature appears and kicks you out of the underworld.The UglyThe main character is a complete ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥.  This guy is absolute o fun to play unless you want to be an ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥.  Even if you follow the ""good"" path everything that comes out of this guys mouth is pure garbage.  Even when you select the nice dialoge option the character sounds like he's♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥off that he even has to talk to someone else.  He has set a new standard for me as most unlikable video game protagonist ever.This game is a disjointed mess.  All of its parts do not equal up to its whole.  Most of its parts are average at best, a few are good, more are bad, and a lot just doesn't make any sense.  All in all, I'm just not really enjoying this game.  Risen 2 was so much better."
