,Recommended,249230,17467097,"Posted: 9 August, 2015",all,Zloth,"A pretty good game for sure!  I got about 60 hours of fun with it using both DLCs.On the plus sideGreat exploration!  They don't limit you so don't be surprised when you finish a quest you didn't even know about yet.Graphics are quite nice.  There's an ""enhanced"" edition rumored but the stock graphics are really quite nice.Good quests.  Organization of the quest log can be a bit dicey (was that an island quest or a crew quest??) but having so many quests that they can be a bit hard to track is a great problem to have.A nice sprinkling of good humor.Mostly bug-free.  There are a few bugs here and there but nothing that really hurt my fun.Good autosave PLUS quick save PLUS named save system.  Why can't all games do this?On the minus sideManual level scaling (see below).Too few monster types.Sea battles start interesting but get tedious.  (Luckily, there's only a few.)Inventory gets too huge to find things.The game is open world and is intent on letting you go wherever you want, with only a few areas locked off.  Unfortunatly, that means that at least half of each island is full of stuff you can defeat with your starting character!  (The fog island DLC is an exception to this.)  So, once you finish a bunch of the first island you go to, the second will be a bit easy and the others will be a LOT easy.  To counter that, you'll need to up the difficulty level as you go along - essentially doing your own level scaling.The game has lots of crafting.  You can craft potions, rum, spell scrolls/stones/dolls, and so on.  I collected TONS of crafting ingredients but I barely used any.  Why?  See the previous paragraph.  Why bother making yourself stronger when the game isn't difficult?While the game has major balance issues as the game goes on, don't let that throw you.  The game is fun!  Just don't make yourself too powerful and keep pushing the difficulty up.  There's much to see and many, many people to chat with!"
