76561197982737666,Not Recommended,249230,17714732,"Posted: 25 August, 2015",all,Siphon,"Don't be fooled by the overall positivity, this game in almost all of its aspects is atrocious.The first and most standout aspect of this game should be the combat; fast paced, exciting, fluid, and interesting combat should be a staple for any game of this type to make up for the long sequences of talking and looting.  Unfortunetly, this game is none of that.  The combat is separated into light and heavy attacks that look no different from each other, (Don't even get me started on the hilariously terrible idea of ""heavy attack"" in swordplay, but I'll spare you my historical rant).  Your light attacks feature a spinning flourish for every single attack except for one that leaves you completely open for counter attack from the VASTLY quicker and deadlier enemies that you face (even the pitifully tiny fish monsters at the start of the game).  Should you choose to string together attacks in a combo your strikes will become progressivly slower until the final strike where the enemy would sooner die from boredom while it waits for the attack. Dodgeing is neccissary but commically utilized, and the ""parry"" system is downright useless when compared to rolling around like an idiot with invincibility frames.  Secondary weapons are consumable and boring in excecution.Bottom line for combat is that it's unintuitive, boring, and most importantly just not fun in any way.Then we have the story.  The plot takes after ""video game trope A-4"" in the fact that it does almost nothing new in its excecution.  Demon overloard was woken up from a nap and now he's cranky, as the player character only you can stop him because why not?  I will say that the distinction between reality and the spirit realm was entertaining for a momment before I realized it had no impact whatsoever on how I played the game.Bottom line for plot is that it's only a background for tearing into new land for looting, no real significance to how you play the game.Sound track isn't noteworthy, while it does serve as an adequate filler.Animations are stiff and cringeworthy. Seems like they poured all of their budget into the spinny dance techniques the character employs in his swordplay.The only reason I would ever have to want to play this game is the hear the protagonist swear at NPC's more.  It's actually really fun to  have a pirate as the protagonist because he has no obligation towards manners, which creates the  exceedingly rare vaguely pleasant momments in the game.Final margin: the game is simply bad.  It's based around systems that are honestly not fun at all.  I bought this game when it was 75% off and only 8 or so Canadian Dollars, and I feel guilty for my idiocy.  I could have just bought a toy cutlass from the dollar store and had ten times the fun this sopping mess of a game gave me.  Please, do not buy this game for any ammount of money."
