76561197978289051,Not Recommended,249230,11682813,"Posted: 12 August, 2014",all,Spectrav,"***Updated*** I was asked to be less vague about the combat issues.Maybe worth $20-$30, graphics and animations are sub par. Not terrible, but nothing special to look at even on max settings.Combat is clunky and boring, I'm one for diffuiculty, but this is just frustrating.The game is unclear to areas you should be going too. Dailogue is so bad an uninteresting, they try to spice it up with curse words.It's not about them holding my hand, I went to the begining island after the intro chapter. I fooled around with getting some new gear at the shop and upgrading some skills. Even with these upgrades I would be 2-3 shot by an enemy.You get a light attack, a medium attack, a cheap shot (your pistol), a parry and a dodge.Light attack- everything is faster than you, the chance of attacking and not getting hit at least a few times is slim. Wouldn't be a problem if I didn't die in a couple of hits.(Yes there are potions, but excessive prices and the amount of damage you take eats up your money fairly quickly)Heavy attack- needs to charge and is slow, 75% of the time the monster just jumps away from you and you miss.Cheap Shot- This is kind of cool, but damage is weak and you only have a finite amount of ammo or throwing knifes.Parry- this is useless most of the time, even an enemies light attack can break your guard and since most enemies double attack you get hit anyway. A parry is supposed to break the momentum of enemies opening them for an attack. This is a crappy block function at best.Dodge- My least favorite mechanic, your recovery time almost always leads to you getting hit by a follow up attack or another enemy.You end up just blocking and dodging waiting for your companion to kill things. I don't need to be the god of war, but I don't appreciate being a punching bag either.The real draw back to the dialogue is the horrible animations, making it almost unbearable to sit through even a 30 second engagement.I'm sure the game gets better, but almost 2 hours in and I can't even stand to look at it anymore. Reminds me of two worlds, if you remember what that was like I would steer clear of this title.In short I would not recomend buying this until it goes on sale and only if you are an older style rpg fan, or you really enjoy the series."
