,Recommended,249230,18659222,"Posted: 24 October, 2015",all,DMINATOR,"Overall the game is ok, fairly long playing time with good RPG elements.Positive:+  Graphically it is pretty good, with latest patch they've improved texture resolutions. FPS does drop when everything is maxed out.+ Story is fine. At least I didn't forget what I was supposed to do, when playing this game only 1-2 times a week+ Minigames. Although simple, some of them are pretty fun to play.+ Exploration. The game always encourages you to look for something special that is hidden near by. It is a very rewarding experience+ Map design, overall pretty good and with a nice variety.Negative:- Combat. The most frustrating combat experience ever. I couldn't find any other game where combat experience was that bad. Controls have a lot of delay, some keys don't register so you have to mash the buttons multiple times to make sure it will. The overall dodge mechanic is just annoying and doesn't make the combat fun in any way. In fact, while you are dodging you are complete invulnerable to damage ? Batman Arkham series have shown what a good fun and fluit combat should be like, take notice Piranha Bytes !- AI. I don't even know if there is an AI in this game. Pretty much all the enemies just charge straight towards you, and go into attack/dodge cycle. Funny thing almost every single monster in the game behaves pretty much the same way, shouldn't there be a better variation of enemy AI, maybe ? Companions pretty much the same thing, while they do follow you, sometimes they just get stuck and become missing, or they go and run away from you, just to hit a monster. And why enemy AI always targets me first ? The fact that I have companions doesn't seem to matter to them.- Glitchy and buggy, for some reason the game kept crashing on me, I occasionally get stuck in the walls, enemies don't care and just go through them. Many other minor issues as well.- Difficulty spikes. In the beginning when you are going with melee, you are going to be destroyed a lot. In the end when you go with magic you are going to destroy everything so easily that game becomes extremely easy. Shouldn't there be a different difficulty curve, like easy in the beginning and harder in the end instead ?"
