76561198070466293,Recommended,249230,14841746,"Posted: 11 March, 2015",all,BloodFFox,"Recomended mostly for the rock-solid fans of Gothic / Risen series.Piranha bytes classics. People blame it for not developing with this gen RPG´s. No way, this is no Skyrim when you are born a hero, this is no Assasin´s creed where you are born with skills to fight 10 enemies at once and crush them. You can reach such status in this game, but it takes time.Simply said you have to EARN your glory step by step, making it a hard work, but a rewarding one, offering a challenge on every difficulty, making the victories against every monsters count early on in the game.I personaly didn´t like the sea battles, they were... odd. Exploring the world is fun, if you´re an eager quest hunter you find yourself in this game, just as in every series made by PB. According to my time played i´m roughly beyond 20% of the world exploration, not mentioning hundreds of pending quests and main storyline not even properly started."
76561197996185138,Recommended,249230,14661317,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,TNT,How do I disable the Friendly Fire.... I feel pity for the follower who slept wrong bed . Everytime my sword hit him as enemy and he cried out loud...
,Recommended,249230,14731306,"Posted: 2 March, 2015",all,Zgragselus,"One of the best RPGs in recent years. Honestly I'm not sure to which game should I compare it, each Piranha Bytes game is its own experience, and I love them for that.I loved all games in Gothic series and I love all games in Risen series. From the Risen series, I would say that Risen 3 is probably the best one of them, even comparable to the golden Gothic 2.The story of this game is solid, it is not the best, not the worst. I've been quite used to bad stereotype-like stories in RPGs (especially open world ones), like TES series, Two Worlds series, or Dragon Age series (in case of more linear ones). Each of these games suffer from black-and-white storyline (from the named ones I consider the plot one of the better ones).The gameplay is typical for Piranha Bytes games. The combat system is something different, and very good (unless you just left-click all day long, which is a bad way to play this game and it can ruin your experience). It is better than in TES games, way better compared to Dragon Age series, but a lot worse compared to Dark Messiah of Might and Magic.In this game you can actually dodge hits (which is very common in medeival fencing schools), but well, don't expect realistic fight simulator. But it is action enough, you won't get bored. Plus, guns are very good addition into the game.Dialogue lines are well done, audio for them is also quite good. As for the quests, there is a whole lot of them, but I'd like more impact on game in general, and longer side quest lines. Music is one of the best, it perfectly suits the game.Visuals are also very good, very nice fire particles, water splashes and particle effects in general. The authors did quite a job on light and shadows, each single island is in a bit different stylized art set and it works perfectly. The graphics quality can compete with any other AAA game.Of course there are few things that look bad. One of them is, that after performing major actions to close gates to underworld, the islands look unchanged. For me, if green grass would return to that areas it would be perfect. I would see that I did some major impact on game world and it would made me even more happy.Second thing is, I don't really see further lore connection with Risen series, yes it is in the same world, there are some of the characters that were in previous games, but the lore connection is weak. I'm comparing mainly to Gothic 1 - Gothic 2 games here, where the lore connection between those game was really strong and good.Anyways, this game is worth it. I know it seems average, it isn't. Don't believe metacritic, as some fans of older Piranha Bytes games are downvoting, without even playing it, sadly..."
,Recommended,249230,14732162,"Posted: 2 March, 2015",all,Chosen Moose,"I think this game is brilliant :) It's got a Fable/Skyrim/Assassins Creed feel to it and personally I'm loving the combat system. I read a lot of reviews saying it was a Con and not a Pro and that scared me a bit but since it was half off I bought it anyway, and I couldn't be happier with it. The combat system is just a timing based system which requires that you read your opponent when battling them. I think that's cool and realistic really. You can riposte others attacks (turn their attack around on them) even to large monsters like golems n stuff which I think is cool, they're coming in with some massive smash attack and ur just like, NOPE *slap*. Great game. Sure I'm only 30 hours in but I think it's lovely. I'm currently a fire wizard dressed up all cool like, runnin around like prince Zuco, burning like 3-4 enemies at once, raining fire down upon my enemies! >:D and when fire doesn't work, LIGHTNING!! Anyway, if you're up for a fun single player RPG, this is a good pick.My only Con: I wish games like these could be Co-op. (Divinity: OS and Dying light for example, also great games that are Co-op.)"
