,Recommended,249230,14024794,"Posted: 16 January, 2015",all,Maciej Medyk,"Risen 3 got a lot of bad reviews and I totally disagree with them. I understand that the combat system may be difficult to some but it wasnt that bad. Dark Souls combat is much harder but people love it. Nevertheless, Risen 3 does a lot of good things and developers did learn a lot from Risen 2 mistakes. Lets go over what are strengths and weaknesses of the game.Pros- Great open world that you can explore at your will. There are 5 islands and you can truly start exploring any one of them.- Great visuals. There is variety of environments from jungles, hils, farms, mines, and lava rivers.- Magic is back. There is crystal mage magic, warrior rune magic, and natives voodoo magic.- There are sea battles with monsters and ships.- There are boss battles that require certain tactics.- Glory advancement system.- Better, more varied faces.Cons- Large difficulty curve. Some may be turned off how weak player is in the begining.- DLC should have been included as they were available on release.Overall it is a very good game. If you play Gothics or Risen games you probably already have it.It is entertaining game that once I started playing I didnt put down until I finished it.Overal Score 8/10 - Good Game."
